    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/prior-literature-synthesis",
      "type": "uofa:Evidence",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior FEA and bench-testing literature for pedicle screw constructs",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior studies examining FEA validation of spinal implant constructs under ASTM F1717 loading conditions. This body of evidence encompasses cadaveric studies, multi-laboratory round-robin bench tests, and previously published FEA-to-experiment comparisons for titanium pedicle screw systems across a range of screw diameters (5.5–8.5 mm) and rod materials. The synthesis establishes the empirical basis for the 10% acceptance bound and the choice of E/uval < 1.96 as a threshold, drawing on convergent findings across at least seven independent research groups over the period 2005–2020. The breadth and consistency of this prior work substantially increases confidence that the acceptance criteria applied in the current COU are well-calibrated to the relevant failure modes."
    },
    {
